  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Extensive tumour debulking challenges both surgeon and anaesthesiologist but promotes
      survival in late-stage ovarian cancer patients. Little is known about the intraoperative
      fluid balance and its impact on morbidity and mortality.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
